│                                                                               │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The crash occurs inside SLPVectorizer during computeMinimumValueSizes when it │
│ attempts to analyze nodes for potential bitwidth demotion. The assertion in   │
│ llvm::cast<Instruction> fails because the code unconditionally casts Values   │
│ from E.Scalars to Instruction, but some Scalars are not Instructions (e.g.,   │
│ PoisonValue or Constants). In this reproducer, the SLP tree includes a poison │
│ value for a UDiv node, and the demotion checker casts it to Instruction       │
│ without guarding, triggering the assertion.                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ The debug log shows SLP analyzing func_125 and building bundles involving     │
│ trunc, bswap, and udiv nodes. A key excerpt lists:                            │
│ - Scalars for a node include "i64 poison".                                    │
│ Immediately after, the pass proceeds to check users and prepare for demotion, │
│ culminating in the crash:                                                     │
│ - Assertion failure in Casting.h at cast<Instruction>(V) within               │
│ BoUpSLP::collectValuesToDemote lambda at SLPVectorizer.cpp:18000.             │
│ This corresponds to the UDiv/URem demotion checker block that does not guard  │
│ against PoisonValue, unlike other checkers (Shl, LShr, AShr) which do have    │
│ such guards.                                                                  │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ Within BoUpSLP::collectValuesToDemote, several opcode-specific demotion       │
│ checkers iterate E.Scalars and cast each Value to Instruction (auto *I =      │
│ cast<Instruction>(V)). Many of these lambdas correctly handle PoisonValue and │
│ return true early, avoiding the cast:                                         │
│ - ShlChecker, LShrChecker, AShrChecker all check isa<PoisonValue>(V).         │
│ However, the UDiv/URem checker at lines 17996–18008 does not check for        │
│ PoisonValue before casting, so when Scalars contain a poison,                 │
│ cast<Instruction>(V) asserts. Similarly, the CallIntrinsics demotion checkers │
│ (CompChecker and AbsChecker) also unconditionally cast to Instruction without │
│ poison guards. The reproducer shows SLP creating a node for udiv with a       │
│ poison scalar, thus hitting the cast in the UDiv/URem checker.                │
│ Therefore, the fix is to make these checkers robust by handling PoisonValue   │
│ (and potentially Constants) before attempting to cast to Instruction,         │
│ consistent with other opcode handlers.                                        │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ - Edit 1 (UDiv/URem checker): Add a guard for PoisonValue before cast.        │
│   File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp, lines 17998–18004    │
│   Change the lambda to:                                                       │
│     return all_of(E.Scalars, [&](Value *V) {                                  │
│       if (isa<PoisonValue>(V))                                                │
│         return true;                                                          │
│       auto *I = cast<Instruction>(V);                                         │
│       APInt Mask = APInt::getBitsSetFrom(OrigBitWidth, BitWidth);             │
│       return MaskedValueIsZero(I->getOperand(0), Mask, SimplifyQuery(*DL)) && │
│              MaskedValueIsZero(I->getOperand(1), Mask, SimplifyQuery(*DL));   │
│     });                                                                       │
│                                                                               │
│ - Edit 2 (Call comp/min/max checker): Add a guard for PoisonValue before      │
│ cast.                                                                         │
│   File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp, lines 18038–18064    │
│   Change the lambda to start with:                                            │
│     return all_of(E.Scalars, [&](Value *V) {                                  │
│       if (isa<PoisonValue>(V))                                                │
│         return true;                                                          │
│       auto *I = cast<Instruction>(V);                                         │
│       ... (rest unchanged)                                                    │
│     });                                                                       │
│                                                                               │
│ - Edit 3 (Call abs checker): Add a guard for PoisonValue before cast.         │
│   File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp, lines 18067–18079    │
│   Change similarly:                                                           │
│     return all_of(E.Scalars, [&](Value *V) {                                  │
│       if (isa<PoisonValue>(V))                                                │
│         return true;                                                          │
│       auto *I = cast<Instruction>(V);                                         │
│       ... (rest unchanged)                                                    │
│     });                                                                       │
│                                                                               │
│ These edits mirror the established pattern in other demotion checkers and     │
│ prevent invalid casts when encountering poison in Scalars.                    │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ The crash is caused by missing PoisonValue guards in demotion checkers for    │
│ UDiv/URem and certain Call intrinsics, leading to an invalid                  │
│ cast<Instruction>(V) when Scalars contain poison. Adding early returns for    │
│ PoisonValue in these lambdas aligns behavior with other opcode handlers and   │
│ avoids the assertion, allowing SLP to proceed safely. This should fix the     │
│ SIGABRT and make the pass robust in the presence of poison values.            │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                               │
